title: Getting started
text: Elevation data can acquired New Zealand digital elevation model hosted LINZ Data Service. wrapper function aemetools package. requires API key LINZ. can easily create key LINZ website: https://data.linz.govt.nz/ use function within aemetools package create one. adding .Renviron file. get_dem_value function return elevation lake metres sea level. now create list lake data. used construct AEME object.
code: aemetools::create_linz_key() # Add the LINZ API key to your .Renviron file aemetools::add_linz_key(key = "your_key_here") # Get the elevation of the lake key <- Sys.getenv("LINZ_KEY") elevation <- aemetools::get_dem_value(lat = lat, lon = lon, key = key) elevation # in metres above sea level #> [1] 29 elevation #> [1] 29 # Define lake list lake = list(     name = "Wainamu",     id = 45819,     latitude = lat,     longitude = lon,     elevation = elevation,     depth = depth,     area = area   )

title: Getting started
text: hypsograph data lake, can use input model. critical input model, defines relationship lake area lake elevation. However, hypsograph data, model use simple cone-shaped hypsograph based lake depth area. ideal, work example. Required column names hypsograph data area, elev, depth.  can see, hypsograph simple cone shape. Ideally, detailed hypsograph data lake. information regarding maximum depth lake, surface area estimate volume development, can generate hypsograph using generate_hypsograph function.
code: # Generate a simple hypsograph hypsograph_simple <- data.frame(area = c(area, 0),                           elev = c(elevation, elevation - depth),                          depth = c(0, -depth)) hypsograph_simple #>     area  elev  depth #> 1 152343 29.00   0.00 #> 2      0 15.93 -13.07 # Plot the hypsograph library(ggplot2)  ggplot(hypsograph_simple, aes(x = area, y = elev)) +   geom_line() +   geom_point() +   xlab("Area (m2)") +   ylab("Elevation (m)") +   theme_bw() # Generate a hypsograph hypsograph <- generate_hypsograph(max_depth = depth, surface_area = area,                                   volume_development = 1.4, elev = elevation,                                   ext_elev = 1)  ggplot(hypsograph, aes(x = area, y = elev)) +   geom_line() +   geom_point() +   geom_line(data = hypsograph_simple, aes(x = area, y = elev), linetype = "dashed") +   xlab("Area (m2)") +   ylab("Elevation (m)") +   theme_bw() # Define input list input = list(     init_depth = depth,     hypsograph = hypsograph,     meteo = met,     use_lw = TRUE,     Kw = Kw   )

title: Introduction to AEME
text: AEME package hosts three one-dimensional hydrodynamic models: DYnamic REservoir Simulation Model (DYRESM), General Lake Model (GLM), General Ocean Turbulence Model (GOTM, adapted closed basins application lakes reservoirs). models can coupled corresponding water quality models, DYRESM-CAEDYM (Computational Aquatic Ecosystem Dynamics Model), GLM-AED2 (Aquatic Ecosystem Dynamics Model 2), GOTM-WET (Water Ecosystem Tool). Key aspects AEME package include: Defined S4 class aeme objects Configuration models common standardised inputs Standardised calibration, manipulation visualisation

title: Introduction to AEME
text: aeme object main object AEME package. S4 class contains information required run model. aeme object contains following slots: lake - list object containing information lake (name, id, latitude, longitude, elevation, shape, depth, area) time - list object containing information time (start, stop, time_step, spin_up) configuration - list object containing information configuration (dy_cd, glm_aed, gotm_wet) observations - list object containing information observations (lake, level) inputs - list object containing information inputs () inflows - list object containing information inflows (data, factor) outflows - list object containing information outflows (data, factor, lvl) water_balance - list object containing information water balance configuration (method, use, data) outputs - list object containing information outputs ()

title: Introduction to AEME
text: lake slot contains information lake. list object contains following objects: name - Name lake (character). id - Lake ID (character numeric). latitude - Latitude lake (numeric). provided, latitude calculated centroid shape. longitude - Longitude lake (numeric). provided, longitude calculated centroid shape. elevation - Elevation lake (numeric). shape - Shape lake (sf object). shape lake can represented polygon. centroid polygon used calculate latitude longitude lake. depth - Max depth lake (m) (numeric). Depth area used generate simple hypsographic curve none provided inputs slot. area - Surface area lake (m2) (numeric) Objects bold required building running model.

title: Introduction to AEME
text: time slot contains information time. list object contains following objects: start - Start date simulation (character). start date must format YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS. end - End date simulation (character). end date must format YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS. timestep - Timestep simulation (numeric). timestep must seconds. spin_up - List spin periods simulation model (numeric). spin period must days. spin period period time model run simulation period. spin period used initialise model discarded examining simulation period.

title: Introduction to AEME
text: configuration slot list contains model configurations. includes configurations files hydrodynamic components well aquatic ecosystem model components: Files hydrodynamic ecosystem models.

title: Introduction to AEME
text: observations slot list contains observations -lake (lake) variables (e.g. water temperature, chlorophyll-, dissolved oxygen etc.) water level (level). observations used assess model performance using function also calibrate model using aemetools package. lake observations stored data frame following columns: Date - Date observation (character). date must format YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS. depth - Depth observation (m) (numeric). depth must metres. var - Variable name observation (character). variable names input preparation designed AEME inputs article. value - Value observation (numeric). level observations stored data frame following columns: Date - Date observation (character). date must format YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS. value - Value observation (numeric).

title: Introduction to AEME
text: aeme object can created YAML file using yaml_to_aeme function. YAML file contains information required run model.

title: Using LERNZmp with AEME
text: Lake Ecosystem Research New Zealand Model Platform (LERNZmp) web platform provides user-friendly interface lake ecosystem model output New Zealand lakes. platform designed provide simple way explore model output across multiple lakes also compare model results observed data. platform located : LERNZmp. Select load lake model output “Overview” tab. model output can downloaded “Download Models” tab. downloads “.zip” folder containing model output selected lake(s) “.rds” files lake metadata file “LERNZmp_lake_metadata.csv”.

title: Using LERNZmp with AEME

title: Using LERNZmp with AEME
text: now build AEME models two lakes using LERNZmp model output. first load AEME object “.rds” files. AEME object contains lake metadata, model output, model controls. details can found vignette("intro-aeme").
code: aeme <- readRDS("lernzmp/LID11133.rds") aeme #>             AEME  #> ------------------------------------------------------------------- #>   Lake #> Rotorua (ID: LID11133); Lat: -38.09; Lon: 176.27; Elev: 284.88m; Depth: 48.15m; #> Area: 80659960 m2; Shape file: Absent #> ------------------------------------------------------------------- #>   Time #> Start: 2013-07-01; Stop: 2023-06-30; Time step: 3600 #>  Spin up (days): GLM: 1095; GOTM: 1095; DYRESM: 1095 #> ------------------------------------------------------------------- #>   Configuration #>     Model controls: Present #>           Physical   |   Biogeochemical #> DY-CD    : Absent     |   Absent  #> GLM-AED  : Present    |   Present #> GOTM-WET : Present    |   Present #> ------------------------------------------------------------------- #>   Observations #> Lake: Present; Level: Absent #> ------------------------------------------------------------------- #>   Input #> Inital profile: Present; Inital depth: 48.148m; Hypsograph: Present (n=95); #> Meteo: Present; Use longwave: TRUE; Kw: 0.5666667 #> ------------------------------------------------------------------- #>   Inflows #> Data: Present; Scaling factors: DY-CD: 1; GLM-AED: 1; GOTM-WET: 1 #> ------------------------------------------------------------------- #>   Outflows #> Data: Present; Scaling factors: DY-CD: 1; GLM-AED: 1; GOTM-WET: 1 #> ------------------------------------------------------------------- #>   Water balance #> Method: 2; Use: obs; Modelled: Absent; Water balance: Present #> ------------------------------------------------------------------- #>   Parameters:  #> Number of parameters: 18 #> ------------------------------------------------------------------- #>   Output:  #> Number of ensembles: 1 #> DY-CD:    1 #> GLM-AED:  1 #> GOTM-WET: 1 model <- c("glm_aed", "gotm_wet") path <- "aeme" # directory in which the model configuration will be built  aeme <- build_aeme(aeme = aeme, model = model, path = path,                     use_aeme = TRUE, use_bgc = TRUE) #> Building simulation for Rotorua [2024-11-11 04:28:21] #> Building existing configuration for Rotorua [2024-11-11 04:28:21] #> Missing state variables in inflows: CHM_oxy, NIT_don, NIT_pon, CAR_doc, CAR_poc, SIL_rsi, PHY_cyano, PHY_green, PHY_diatom, NCS_ss1 #> Added default values for missing variables. #> Missing state variables in inflows: CHM_oxy, NIT_don, NIT_pon, CAR_doc, CAR_poc, SIL_rsi, PHY_cyano, PHY_green, PHY_diatom, NCS_ss1 #> Added default values for missing variables. #> Missing state variables in inflows: CHM_oxy, NIT_don, NIT_pon, CAR_doc, CAR_poc, SIL_rsi, PHY_cyano, PHY_green, PHY_diatom, NCS_ss1 #> Added default values for missing variables. #> Missing state variables in inflows: CHM_oxy, NIT_don, NIT_pon, CAR_doc, CAR_poc, SIL_rsi, PHY_cyano, PHY_green, PHY_diatom, NCS_ss1 #> Added default values for missing variables. #> Missing state variables in inflows: CHM_oxy, NIT_don, NIT_pon, CAR_doc, CAR_poc, SIL_rsi, PHY_cyano, PHY_green, PHY_diatom, NCS_ss1 #> Added default values for missing variables. #> Missing state variables in inflows: CHM_oxy, NIT_don, NIT_pon, CAR_doc, CAR_poc, SIL_rsi, PHY_cyano, PHY_green, PHY_diatom, NCS_ss1 #> Added default values for missing variables. #> Missing state variables in inflows: CHM_oxy, NIT_pon, CAR_doc, CAR_poc, SIL_rsi, PHY_cyano, PHY_green, PHY_diatom, NCS_ss1 #> Added default values for missing variables. #> No water level present. title: Aquatic Ecosystem Model Ensemble
text: Aquatic Ecosystem Model Ensemble (AEME) package allows setup run ensemble aquatic ecosystem models. models DYRESM-CAEDYM, GLM-AED GOTM-WET.

title: Aquatic Ecosystem Model Ensemble
text: package developed LimnoTrack part Lake Ecosystem Restoration New Zealand Modelling Platform (LERNZmp) project.

title: Aquatic Ecosystem Model Ensemble
text: basic example shows build run one models ensemble: model input output handled ’s S4 object class aeme. allows standardisation generalisation functions class alongside ensuring integrity validity ’s structure. allows easier handling model output data within structure allows condensed output printed console: Model data can visualised easily using plot_output() function:  Also, visualising lake level plots.

title: Aeme Class — Aeme
text: class represents data related lake running AEME. Items bold required run models.

title: Aeme Class — Aeme
text: lake list representing lake information. name: character; lake name. id: character; lake identifier. latitude: numeric; lake latitude. longitude: numeric; lake longitude. elevation: numeric; lake elevation. shape: sf; lake shape. depth: numeric; lake depth. area: numeric; lake area. Calculated shape provided. time list representing time information. start: character; start date. stop: character; end date. timestep: numeric; time step. spin_up: list; spin information model configuration list representing model's configuration. model_controls: dataframe; Model controls simulation. dy_cd: list; DYRESM-CAEDYM configuration. glm_aed: list; GLM-AED configuration. gotm_wet: list; GOTM-WET configuration. observations list representing observation information. lake: dataframe; lake observations. level: dataframe; lake level observations. input list representing input information. init_profile: dataframe; initial temperature profile (none use NULL leave empty; empty/NULL, observations file used). init_depth: numeric; initial height lake surface relative bottom (m). hypsograph: dataframe; hypsograph. meteo: dataframe; meteorological data. use_lw: logical; use longwave radiation. Kw: numeric; light extinction coefficient (m-1). inflows list representing inflows information. data: named list inflow dataframes. factor: named list; inflow factors model. outflows list representing outflows information. data: named list outflow dataframes. factor: named list; outflow factors model. lvl: numeric; height lake level outflow. water_balance list representing water balance information. method: integer; Method calculating water balance. 1 = none, 2 = outflows, 3 = inflows outflows. use: character; Can 'obs' 'mod'. Use observations  modelled data water balance. data: list dataframe water balance. output list representing output information. dy_cd: list; DYRESM-CAEDYM output. glm_aed: list; GLM-AED output. gotm_wet: list; GOTM-WET output. parameters dataframe representing model parameters.

code: build_aeme(   aeme = NULL,   config = NULL,   model = c("dy_cd", "glm_aed", "gotm_wet"),   model_controls = NULL,   inf_factor = c(glm_aed = 1, dy_cd = 1, gotm_wet = 1),   outf_factor = c(glm_aed = 1, dy_cd = 1, gotm_wet = 1),   ext_elev = 0,   use_bgc = FALSE,   calc_wbal = TRUE,   calc_wlev = TRUE,   use_aeme = FALSE,   coeffs = NULL,   hum_type = 3,   est_swr_hr = TRUE,   path = "." )

title: Build model configuration directories — build_aeme
text: aeme aeme; object. config list; loaded via `config <- yaml::read_yaml("aeme.yaml")` model vector; models used. Can `dy_cd`, `glm_aed`, `gotm_wet`. model_controls dataframe; configuration loaded "model_controls.csv". inf_factor vector; containing numeric factor multiple inflows. Needs named according model. outf_factor vector; containing numeric factor multiple outflows. Needs named according model. ext_elev numeric; metres extend hypograph . use_bgc logical; switch use biogeochemical model. calc_wbal logical; calculate water balance. Default = TRUE. calc_wlev logical; calculate water level. use_aeme logical; use AEME object generate model confiuration files. coeffs numeric vector length two; used estimate surface water temperature estimating evaporation. Defaults NULL. water temperature observations included `aeme` object, use build linear relationship air temperature water temperature. Otherwise. uses simple estimation  \(temp_water = 5 + 0.75 * temp_air\) Stefan & Preud'homme, 2007:  www.doi.org/10.1111/j.1752-1688.1993.tb01502.x hum_type numeric; GOTM humidity metric [1=relative humidity ( 2=wet-bulb temperature, 3=dew point temperature, 4=specific humidity (kg/kg)] Default = 3. est_swr_hr logical; estimate hourly shortwave radiation daily values. Default = TRUE. path filepath; input files located relative `config`.
